# Annotation Queue Add Calls

Add calls to an annotation queue.

POST

/

annotation_queues

/

{queue_id}

/

items

Annotation Queue Add Calls
    
    
    curl --request POST \
      --url https://api.example.com/annotation_queues/{queue_id}/items \
      --header 'Authorization: Basic <encoded-value>' \
      --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
      --data '
    {
      "project_id": "<string>",
      "call_ids": [
        "<string>"
      ],
      "display_fields": [
        "<string>"
      ]
    }
    '
    
    
    {
      "added_count": 123,
      "duplicates": 123
    }

#### Authorizations

HTTPBasicHTTPBearerHTTPBasicHTTPBearer

​

Authorization

string

header

required

Basic authentication header of the form `Basic <encoded-value>`, where `<encoded-value>` is the base64-encoded string `username:password`.

#### Path Parameters

​

queue_id

string

required

#### Body

application/json

Request body for adding calls to an annotation queue (queue_id comes from path).

​

project_id

string

required

Example:

`"entity/project"`

​

call_ids

string[]

required

Example:
    
    
    ["call-1", "call-2", "call-3"]

​

display_fields

string[]

required

JSON paths to display to annotators

Example:
    
    
    ["input.prompt", "output.text"]

#### Response

Successful Response

Response from adding calls to a queue.

​

added_count

integer

required

​

duplicates

integer

required

